UPDATE locations SET description = 'One of the Canary Islands` top windsurf destinations. Pozo Izquierdo hosts the PWA World Cup and is famous for its powerful side-shore winds and big wave sailing. The southeast coast offers consistent trade winds from spring through autumn, making it ideal for advanced sailors seeking challenging conditions.' WHERE id = 1;

UPDATE locations SET description = 'The largest Canary Island offers reliable trade winds and warm waters year-round. El Médano is the main windsurf hub, with a long sandy beach and consistent side-shore winds. The spot suits all levels and has a vibrant windsurf community, surf schools, and easy access to gear rental.' WHERE id = 2;

UPDATE locations SET description = 'A world-class windsurf destination in the Canary Islands, known for the legendary Sotavento lagoon. Consistent trade winds blow from April to October, with flat water on the inside and waves on the outside. Fuerteventura offers spots for every level, from beginners at Costa Calma to experts at Risco del Paso.' WHERE id = 3;

UPDATE locations SET description = 'The French Mediterranean coast from Gruissan to Hyères is a windsurfing paradise shaped by the Mistral and Tramontane winds. Almanarre near Hyères offers flat water freestyle, while Gruissan and Leucate deliver powerful gusty conditions. The region combines great wind with French culture, food, and sunny weather.' WHERE id = 4;

UPDATE locations SET description = 'The southernmost tip of Spain, where the Atlantic meets the Mediterranean. Tarifa is Europe''s wind capital, with the Levante and Poniente winds blowing over 300 days a year. Iconic beaches like Valdevaqueros, Los Lances, and Balneario offer everything from flat water to waves. A must-visit for any windsurfer.' WHERE id = 5;

UPDATE locations SET description = 'Northern Italy''s most famous lake windsurf spot, where thermal winds funnel through the Alps. The reliable Ora wind blows every afternoon from the south, while the Peler comes from the north in the morning. Torbole is the main hub with flat water, stunning mountain scenery, and a laid-back Italian atmosphere.' WHERE id = 6;

UPDATE locations SET description = 'The largest Greek island offers strong Meltemi winds during summer, crystal-clear waters, and uncrowded spots. Falasarna on the west coast and Elafonisi in the southwest provide stunning beach settings with reliable wind. Crete combines world-class sailing with ancient history, incredible food, and Mediterranean warmth.' WHERE id = 7;

UPDATE locations SET description = 'The birthplace of modern windsurfing and home to Ho''okipa, one of the most iconic wave-sailing spots on the planet. Maui''s north shore delivers consistent trade winds and powerful Pacific swells. Kanaha is the go-to spot for freeriding and freestyle, while Ho''okipa is reserved for expert wave sailors.' WHERE id = 8;

UPDATE locations SET description = 'An unexpected windsurf gem in the heart of Europe. Swiss lakes like Silvaplana, Urnersee, and Lake Garda offer thermal winds surrounded by breathtaking alpine scenery. The Maloja wind at Silvaplana is legendary for its reliability in summer. Fresh water, mountain views, and a unique windsurf experience.' WHERE id = 9;

UPDATE locations SET description = 'Home to some of the most consistent and powerful wind conditions in the Southern Hemisphere. Geraldton and Lancelin offer world-class wave sailing and flat-water blasting with the Fremantle Doctor sea breeze. Western Australia delivers remote, uncrowded spots with warm water and reliable summer winds.' WHERE id = 10;

UPDATE locations SET description = 'A North Sea beach town in the Netherlands known for its exposed coastline and powerful winds. Wijk aan Zee offers wave sailing on the open sea, with conditions that can range from mellow to challenging. Popular with Dutch and German windsurfers looking for North Sea action close to Amsterdam.' WHERE id = 11;

UPDATE locations SET description = 'A stunning beach on the Pembrokeshire coast in Wales, backed by dramatic cliffs. Newgale picks up Atlantic swells and westerly winds, offering a mix of wave riding and bump-and-jump conditions. The beach is wide and sandy, and the scenery is spectacular — a rugged, wild windsurf experience in the UK.' WHERE id = 12;

UPDATE locations SET description = 'A powerful wave-sailing destination on Denmark''s northwest coast, facing the North Sea. Hanstholm delivers big swells and strong winds, attracting experienced sailors who love cold-water wave sailing. The spot is exposed and can be challenging, but rewards with epic conditions and an adventurous Scandinavian setting.' WHERE id = 13;

UPDATE locations SET description = 'One of the best beach breaks on England''s south coast, located in West Sussex. West Wittering offers clean waves and good wind exposure from the southwest. The sandy beach and shallow waters make it accessible, while stronger days deliver solid bump-and-jump conditions. A favourite among UK windsurfers.' WHERE id = 14;

UPDATE locations SET description = 'A remote and dramatic windsurf spot on Norway''s west coast. Vigra Nausta sits on an island exposed to the North Atlantic, delivering powerful winds and waves in a wild, Nordic landscape. For adventurous sailors seeking raw, uncrowded conditions in one of Europe''s most spectacular settings.' WHERE id = 15;

UPDATE locations SET description = 'Another Canary Island gem with volcanic landscapes and consistent trade winds. Lanzarote offers a variety of spots from flat-water lagoons to wave-sailing beaches. Costa Teguise and Famara are the main windsurf areas. The island''s unique terrain, warm climate, and steady winds make it a great year-round destination.' WHERE id = 16;

UPDATE locations SET description = 'An emerging windsurf destination with consistent Atlantic trade winds, warm water, and uncrowded spots. Dakhla and Essaouira are the main hubs — Dakhla''s lagoon offers flat water and steady wind, while Essaouira delivers waves and a vibrant Moroccan atmosphere. Great value and reliable conditions.' WHERE id = 17;

UPDATE locations SET description = 'A Greek island in the Aegean Sea known for strong Meltemi winds during summer. Prasonisi at the southern tip is the star spot, where the Aegean meets the Mediterranean creating both flat water and wave conditions on either side of a narrow sand strip. Rhodes combines great wind with Greek island charm.' WHERE id = 18;

UPDATE locations SET description = 'The Turkish Aegean coast offers warm waters, reliable thermal and Meltemi winds, and affordable living. Alaçatı near Çeşme is the main windsurf hub, famous for its flat-water bay and consistent summer winds. Turkey combines excellent sailing conditions with rich culture, great food, and welcoming hospitality.' WHERE id = 19;

UPDATE locations SET description = 'One of the windiest cities on Earth, located at the tip of Africa where the Atlantic and Indian oceans collide. Table Bay, Blouberg, and Langebaan offer everything from flat water to powerful waves. The strong southeast ''Cape Doctor'' wind blows reliably from October to March, making Cape Town a world-class windsurf destination.' WHERE id = 20;

UPDATE locations SET description = 'A rising star in the Asian windsurf scene, with Mui Ne as the main destination. Consistent northeast monsoon winds from November to April create ideal conditions over warm, turquoise waters. Mui Ne offers flat water near shore and waves further out, plus excellent value for accommodation and gear rental.' WHERE id = 21;

UPDATE locations SET description = 'A small Caribbean island known for its crystal-clear waters and consistent trade winds. Lac Bay is the star spot — a shallow, warm-water lagoon with steady side-shore wind, perfect for freestyle and freeride. Bonaire offers a tropical windsurf paradise with incredible underwater life and a relaxed island vibe.' WHERE id = 22;
